From 4af73f8a059dc25f542f3e78873f5109403eb737 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andre Eikmeyer <dev@deq.rocks>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 02:54:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] thunderbolt: Apple T2 Titan Ridge systems need resume
 ordering links

Apple T2 Macs with Titan Ridge controllers lose their Thunderbolt PCIe
tunnels during S3. The NHI must resume before the tunneled downstream
ports so it can rebuild those tunnels before their consumers resume.

The driver already establishes this ordering on older Apple Thunderbolt
controllers. Titan Ridge uses the same discrete switch topology, but its
NHI IDs are absent from the Apple-specific match.

The missing ordering leaves bridges waiting for several seconds during
resume and also delays secondary CPU bring-up. Repeated S3 cycles on a
MacBookPro15,1 reduced CPU bring-up from 12-15 seconds to about one second
once the complete T2 suspend fix was active.

Signed-off-by: Andre Eikmeyer <dev@deq.rocks>
---
 drivers/thunderbolt/tb.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/thunderbolt/tb.c b/drivers/thunderbolt/tb.c
index 76323255439a..c5f2d151a018 100644
--- a/drivers/thunderbolt/tb.c
+++ b/drivers/thunderbolt/tb.c
@@ -3323,6 +3323,8 @@ static bool tb_apple_add_links(struct tb_nhi *nhi)
 	case PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_CACTUS_RIDGE_4C:
 	case PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_FALCON_RIDGE_2C_NHI:
 	case PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_FALCON_RIDGE_4C_NHI:
+	case PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_TITAN_RIDGE_2C_NHI:
+	case PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_TITAN_RIDGE_4C_NHI:
 		break;
 	default:
 		return false;
-- 
